Job Title: Senior Insights Analyst - Gain Gen AI - Campaign/Marketing.
Ad Text:
Senior Insights Analyst – Sydney - $180,000 - Gain Gen AI - Strong Career Development

Tech and Data People are partnering with a respected organisation seeking a Lead Insights Analyst to join their business performance and analytics function. This is a senior individual contributor role, delivering insight-driven analysis to support strategic and operational decision-making across a complex, data-rich environment.

About the Role:

You will work closely with finance, marketing, and campaign teams to provide actionable insights through reporting, analysis, and data interpretation. The role involves collaborating with stakeholders to influence strategy and optimise business performance using modern analytics tools.

What You Will Do:

Deliver insightful reporting and dashboards aligned with organisational KPIs and OKRs
Analyse key business drivers and support strategic initiatives through scenario and sensitivity modelling
Partner with business units including finance and marketing to provide actionable insights
Support the development and tracking of commercial policies and frameworks
Champion the use of analytics tools to enhance decision-making and data literacy
Maintain awareness of emerging AI tools and advise on responsible adoption to support reporting and forecasting
What You Will Bring:

Strong experience in business performance, analytics, or strategic insights roles
Strong skills in data analysis, performance reporting, and commercial analysis
Experience working across finance, marketing, operations, and product data
Ability to influence senior stakeholders and translate data into actionable insights
Exposure to modern analytics platforms and tools
Your Skills:

Strong commercial and analytical acumen
Proficiency in SQL, Power BI, and Excel; working knowledge of Python or R; familiarity with cloud-based platforms such as Databricks
Excellent communication, presentation, and stakeholder management skills
Ability to work independently and deliver high-quality insights in a fast-paced environment
Qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Economics, Business, Data Science, or Mathematics
Postgraduate qualification such as CA, CPA, MBA, or CFA preferred
Why Join:

Gain Gen AI
Work in a data-driven, commercially focused environment
Opportunity to shape insights that influence business strategy and marketing performance
If you are a skilled analyst who thrives at turning data into actionable insights and influencing decision-making, we would love to hear from you. Apply now or reach out for a confidential conversation.

Salary: $150 per hour (inclusive of super or plus GST)
Ad Text:
This is a long term contract role with an Australian Government agency that administers intellectual property (IP) rights and legislation for patents, trade marks, design rights etc

Role Description:

This Lead Digital Experience Business Analyst will work within a multidisciplinary delivery team; following agile principles to support continuous improvement and ongoing maturity of the agency's corporate website.

This will involve working closely with the corporate website product owner, content author, end users, developers and other technical specialists
 
Duties and Responsibilities:
 
Under the direction of the corporate website product team, the BA's tasks will include:

Engaging with business stakeholders to understand their needs and express these as user stories and requirements
Conducting research and in-depth analysis of existing business processes and products.
Collaborating with subject matter experts, end users, product owners, architects, developers and testers to design and deliver solutions.
Sprint planning with delivery teams
Assisting the product owner to run agile ceremonies
Being part of a progressive and modern delivery team responsible for transforming IP Australia's digital services and delivering innovative customer-centric solutions
Contribute to agile/delivery/project management practices
Support an ongoing continuous improvement delivery focus.
Provide technical solution advice to software engineers, data scientists and executive stakeholders  
Skills and Experience: 

Essential:

Exceptional ability to confidently elicit and define requirements & acceptance criteria following best practice principles
Exceptional communication skills and a proven ability to facilitate interviews, undertake workshops and document analysis - as well as work closely with stakeholders in order to elicit needs and develop a shared understanding of current processes
Possess an understanding of digital platforms and content management systems; with the ability to work effectively with developers, architects and product teams
Ability to deliver high quality documentation such as process maps and current/future state diagrams - based on thorough analysis and stakeholder input
Current Baseline Security Clearance
Desirable:

Demonstrated experience and understanding of the intellectual property (IP) ecosystem; including familiarity with key stakeholders, processes and regulatory considerations relevant to IP management and innovation
Demonstrated experience working with Smart IQ
Consultant: Colin Massey

What YOU do matters!

Are you looking to do something that matters? At Benetas, you’ll be part of a diverse, engaging and collaborative culture that is guided by our values of respect, responsibility, community and spirit. Join us and make a difference!
Insights and analytics have never been so important for the health and aged care sector, and this is a fabulous opportunity to join a hard-working team building something big.

Benetas is looking for an experienced researcher for the position of Insights Manager.  The role is responsible for evolving and leading our enterprise-wide insights function at Benetas. The Insights Manager will be responsible for continuing to build an efficient team and delivering meaningful insights on a regular basis to address a wide variety of internal and external stakeholder needs.

About the role

The Insights Manager, together with one direct report, will be responsible for:

Building a deeper understanding of our current and prospective customers and delivering actionable insights to the business which will help inform short- and long-term organisational priorities.
Recruiting and managing our Consumer Advisory Body
Growing awareness of our brand as a thought leader by delivering high quality, innovative, and actionable research for advocacy on issues facing the aged care sector and older people generally.

This role sits on the Leadership team of the Customer, Insights and Marketing team, and reports into the GM, Customer, Insights & Marketing.  The position is located at our Support Office in Hawthorn East, just 10 kilometres from the Melbourne CBD.

About you

Tertiary qualified in quantitative analysis, marketing, market research, psychology or a related field
Extensive experience and knowledge of a range of research activities including sourcing, analysing, and interpreting complex data, designing, and executing qualitative and quantitative market research studies.
Familiar with advanced statistical techniques including conjoint modelling, segmentation and driver analysis
Experienced leader, with confidence to participate, lead and influence team discussions to bring the voice of the consumer into consideration when making decisions
Excellent verbal and written communications skills
Highly developed organisational and time management skills                                                           

 You can look forward to

Permanent part-time employment (0.8 FTE)
Working from home up to two days per week, and in our Support Office in Hawthorn East
Being part of a trusted team within a supportive community
Proudly being part of a business that values Respect, Responsibility, Community, and Spirit
Engaging in meaningful work with a strong commitment to customer experience
Varied role with excellent opportunities to show leadership and develop professionally
Generous salary packaging arrangements including novated car leasing options
Working with an engaged and passionate team

About Benetas:

Benetas is a leading not-for-profit organisation dedicated to actively working with older Victorians, their friends and carers through a range of residential aged care, primary care, and in-home services. We care about our people’s health and well-being and are committed to our reputation as a truly great place to work and volunteer.

The Senior Business Analyst is a critical role responsible for leading the analysis, documentation, and management of business requirements across the project lifecycle. Operating within a lending business, undergoing a significant digital and operational transformation, you will ensure that initiatives are aligned with strategic goals, are scoped effectively, and deliver measurable outcomes.

You will work closely with stakeholders to understand business objectives, translating them into operational improvements and robust technical solutions. This role requires strong analytical thinking, exceptional stakeholder engagement, and the ability to communicate clearly across both business and technical audiences.
 
Key focus:
 
The organisation is currently undertaking a significant upgrade to its lending platform. The Senior Business Analyst will play a key role in shaping and delivering these initiatives, including process optimisation and system enhancements.

Strong domain expertise in lending is essential. This includes a solid understanding of the full loan lifecycle:

Loan Origination
Credit Assessment
Servicing
Collections processes
Experience would ideally span a range of financial products, such as mortgages, auto finance, commercial real estate loans, personal loans, and credit cards.

You should be comfortable translating complex financial requirements into system capabilities, working with data models, and supporting workflows for credit decisioning, regulatory compliance, and customer lifecycle management. Familiarity with lending platforms and loan management systems is highly desirable.
 
Key Responsibilities 

Lead the elicitation, documentation, validation, and management of business and functional requirements.
Conduct requirements and scope reviews to ensure alignment with business goals.
Track and manage changes to requirements and scope throughout the project lifecycle.
Validate requirements and ensure traceability from initiation through to delivery.
Perform gap and change analysis to support strategic decision-making and provide recommendations to senior stakeholders.
Process Design and Improvement

Document current state processes and design future state processes using BPMN standards and agreed tooling.
Evaluate existing processes to identify opportunities for improvement and enhance operational efficiency.
Support the adoption of emerging technologies by identifying relevant use cases.
Maintain all documentation in accordance with organisational standards and frameworks.
Solution Assessment and Vendor Engagement

Conduct solution assessments and compare proposed options against defined criteria.
Support the vendor selection processes, including establishing evaluation criteria and reviewing proposals to form recommendations.
Collaborate with business and project teams to assess vendor capabilities and alignment with business needs.
Analyse market trends and perform needs assessments to inform solution design and investment decisions.
** 5 days a week in the office in Sydney **

The Company
Our client is a global leader in financial services, known for its industry-leading digital banking, wealth management, and business banking services. Operating in multiple markets worldwide with a strong track record of profitability, the organisation thrives on its commitment to innovation and empowering its people to make a difference. The company fosters a diverse and inclusive culture where employees are encouraged to drive outcomes and contribute to the success of the business.

The Leaders
You will report into the Reward Advisory Lead and join a high-performing, collaborative team of reward professionals, analysts, and project leads. The leaders in this space are commercial, data-driven, and outcome-focused, with a collaborative and flexible working style. While the team is fast-paced and delivery-oriented, they offer guidance and open communication, with a strong emphasis on delivering high-quality outputs.

The Opportunity
As a Reward Advisor, you will play a critical role in supporting the business  in the annual remuneration review process and process improvement. You will utilise your technical capability and stakeholder engagement skills to deliver business-critical outcomes within a global and complex environment. You will provide both analytical and advisory support, with exposure to global reward cycles, modelling and governance work.

Key responsibilities:

Support the end-to-end remuneration review process, including data collation, analysis and reporting
Deliver reward advice and insights to P&C and business stakeholders
Manage modelling and scenario analysis to inform recommendations
Liaise with internal global stakeholders across London, New York and Asia
Assist with technical reward work including carried interest (desirable, but not essential)
Balance BAU delivery with ad hoc project-based initiatives
Partner with internal clients to solve business challenges
Potential to support process improvements and develop documentation across reward frameworks
Provide input into governance, policy development and reward operations
About You
You are a capable, data-driven reward professional who can step into a high-performing team and deliver value. You bring proven experience in reward advisory, human resources or finance, ideally within a global matrixed organisation.

You are commercially astute, with a strong ability to translate complex data into actionable insights. You thrive in ambiguity, enjoy delivering both strategic and operational outcomes, and are comfortable working on global initiatives.
This role will particularly suit someone who enjoys getting into the detail, can pick up tasks quickly with minimal instruction, and is looking to make a tangible impact in a short time frame. 

The Process
The process will consist of an initial meeting with a Levyl consultant, followed by two rounds of interviews and psychometric testing as part of the selection process. Candidates will also be subject to background and reference checks.

For any confidential enquiries, please contact Antony Jones on 0448 198 544 or antony@levyl.com.au

Levyl encourage diverse, equitable and inclusive recruitment solutions and commit to respond to every applicant. We make selection and shortlist decisions based on your skills, experience, personal attributes, and motivators. Should you be successful for interview, we will tender you an interview accommodation checklist, so that you can let us know how we can support you to perform at your best.

The Role

We need a senior Business Analyst to lead our BA team and become the expert on OmniStar, our grants, ethics and research management platform for government agencies and universities.

You'll manage a team of analysts, work directly with enterprise clients on complex requirements, and handle the analysis work that needs senior experience. This is a hands-on role - you'll be deep in the product, setting standards for the team, and working closely with developers to design and document features.




The Job

You'll develop deep expertise in OmniStar and lead a team of 6-8 business analysts. You'll work directly with government agencies and universities to design and document features for complex web applications. You'll set quality standards, mentor team members, and work closely with our development team to translate business needs into technical solutions.

This means running workshops with senior stakeholders, eliciting requirements for complicated compliance workflows, creating detailed specifications, and making sure nothing falls through the cracks. You'll review team deliverables, handle difficult client conversations, and guide decisions on projects.

The platform handles research grants, ethics approvals, and compliance tracking for government agencies and universities. Our clients need detailed requirements documentation, careful process design, and solutions that meet strict compliance standards. Experience with government, healthcare, research, or finance environments will be directly applicable.




What We Need

10+ years doing Business Analysis or Systems Analysis in software development

You've led, managed, or mentored analysts before

Technical understanding - you can talk to developers about databases, APIs, and system architecture

Government or complex stakeholder experience - public sector, universities, or heavily regulated industries

Expert at documentation - your specs are clear and comprehensive

Workshop facilitation skills - you can run a room and extract requirements from difficult stakeholders

Process modelling experience (UML, BPMN, etc.)

Worked in Agile environments

Australian citizenship (required for security clearance eligibility)

What we'd love to see:

Existing Australian government security clearance (we can sponsor if you don't have one)

Experience with grants, research administration, ethics, or compliance systems

SQL or database skills

Background in SaaS platforms with multiple client implementations

What actually matters most: You have sound judgement. You work independently. You understand things the first time. You know when to push back and when to compromise. Developers respect your input because you understand constraints. Nothing slips through the cracks on your watch.




About F1 Solutions

We're a 30-year-old Australian software company in Canberra. We build OmniStar for government and university clients across Australia and internationally.

Meaningful work, technical depth, and autonomy. We're stable (30+ years, ongoing government contracts), we support professional development (IIBA, Agile certifications), and we're realistic about work-life balance.

We don't have ping pong tables or unlimited snacks. We do have interesting technical problems, sophisticated clients, and the opportunity to shape solutions rather than just execute someone else's plan.

This role is onsite in Canberra.




How to Apply

Email your CV and a one-page cover letter to jobs@f1solutions.com

Tell us:

Why you want to become an OmniStar subject matter expert

An example of a complex stakeholder situation you navigated

How you develop junior analysts

Your availability and security clearance status

We respond within 48 hours. Strong candidates will go through a phone screen, technical interview (we'll test your analytical thinking with real scenarios), and final discussion. We move fast - application to offer can be under two weeks. We review on a rolling basis. Don't wait if you're interested.

Questions? Email jobs@f1solutions.com before applying.
